The paper deals with the properties and variational equalities of directed information, which is a concept commonly used in information theory and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also utilizes concepts from topology and functional analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
